  "texts": [
    "In this sense, one has to acknowledge the limited function of the GDPR as a data protection framework; it is not a panacea for any issue raised by automation.",
    "168 Third, it provides normative arguments to delimit their employment or require additional safeguards for fundamental rights-compliant use.",
    "For instance, transparency in automated evidencewhich goes beyond \"the logic involved\" and requires understandability and access to the criteria and operations of the programscan be derived from the right to an effective remedy.",
    "The case law of the CJEU on risk assessments in border control is an important reminder of the role of fundamental rights beyond data protection law in the automation era.",
    "In all three cases, the Court was asked to assess the compatibility of EU law (Opinion 1/15 and Ligue de Droit) or national law (La Quadrature du Net) with the right to privacy and data protection enshrined in Articles 7 and 8 of the CFREU."
